# Copy to .env and fill in your values. Do NOT commit .env.

# REQUIRED — your Anthropic API key for post analysis
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHO WE TRACK
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The roster of tracked analysts lives in ONE place: the REGISTRY in
# lib/analysts.ts. Each entry declares its display name and, per platform,
# the account handle (e.g. { x: 'realDonaldTrump', truthsocial: 'realDonaldTrump' }).
# To add a target — or add a platform to an existing one — edit that registry.
# The env vars below are NOT how you choose who to track; see their notes.

# Optional ops escape hatch — comma-separated X handles to track, replacing the
# built-in default roster WITHOUT a code change. Use this only for a quick
# X-only roster swap at deploy time; the curated registry is the real source.
#
# Caveats: handles added here are tracked on X ONLY (no Truth Social) and render
# with their @handle as the display name — UNLESS the handle matches a registry
# entry, in which case that entry's metadata + platforms are inherited. Anything
# multi-platform or with custom display metadata must live in lib/analysts.ts.
# TRACKED_HANDLES=aleabitoreddit,realDonaldTrump

# Optional — LEGACY attribution only. NOT a tracking selector. Read in exactly
# one place (lib/db.ts) to backfill the `author` column on old rows that predate
# multi-analyst support. Changing it does NOT add or remove a tracked account.
TWITTER_USERNAME=aleabitoreddit

# Optional — IANA timezone for container logs (default: UTC). Also anchors the
# daily digest cron: DIGEST_HOUR is interpreted in this timezone.
TZ=America/New_York

# Optional — hour (0–23, server-local per TZ) the daily digest brief is
# generated. Default 8 (08:00). The digest is one batched Claude request that
# summarizes the trailing 24h of posts into the dashboard's headline brief.
DIGEST_HOUR=8

# Optional — host port to expose the app on (default: 3737)
# Change this if 3737 is taken on your machine. The container always
# listens on 3000 internally; this only affects the host-side binding.
PORT_HOST=3737

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fresh-tweet path via RSSHub (opt-in)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The free Twitter syndication endpoint is increasingly cached for many
# individual accounts (months stale). RSSHub can scrape live data but the
# current /twitter/user/:id route needs all THREE values below.
#
# Without these, RSSHub returns 503 and the app silently falls back to
# syndication — so populating these is opt-in.

# 1) AUTH TOKEN — the `auth_token` cookie from a logged-in browser session.
#    How to get: log into x.com in any browser → open DevTools (F12) →
#    Application → Cookies → x.com → copy the value of the `auth_token`
#    cookie. It looks like a 40-char hex string.
#    SECURITY: this cookie is equivalent to a login session — only use a
#    sacrificial / throwaway account, never your real one.
TWITTER_AUTH_TOKEN=

# 2 & 3) CONSUMER KEY + SECRET — from a Twitter Developer App.
#    How to get:
#      a. Go to https://developer.x.com and apply for an account (free tier).
#      b. After approval, create a new Project + App.
#      c. In the App's "Keys and tokens" tab, copy the "API Key" (consumer
#         key) and "API Key Secret" (consumer secret).
#    The Free dev tier is usually enough for read-only timeline access.
TWITTER_CONSUMER_KEY=
TWITTER_CONSUMER_SECRET=

# To disable the RSSHub path entirely (always use syndication):
# RSSHUB_URL=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Truth Social (opt-in, via the bundled sidecar)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Analysts with a `platforms.truthsocial` acct in lib/analysts.ts (e.g. Trump)
# also pull their Truth Social posts, merged into the same source (a per-post
# platform tag distinguishes them on each card). Truth Social blocks
# plain server requests at Cloudflare, so the `truthsocial` Compose service
# fetches them via browser TLS impersonation (no credentials needed for
# prominent public accounts). Defaults to the in-network service URL.
# To disable Truth Social entirely, set this empty:
# TRUTHSOCIAL_URL=
#
# Override the Chrome TLS impersonation targets if Cloudflare starts blocking
# (newest-first; first to clear wins):
# TS_IMPERSONATE=chrome146,chrome136,chrome131

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STATIC EXPORT — GitHub Pages
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The read-only GitHub Pages snapshot (on-demand analysis disabled; daily
# digest baked in). See README "Publishing to GitHub Pages".
#
# Manual one-off deploy from the host (reads the LOCAL data/serenity.db):
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_STATIC_EXPORT=1      # set automatically by build:static
#   PAGES_REMOTE=origin              # remote name or URL to push to
#   PAGES_BRANCH=gh-pages            # branch GitHub Pages serves from
#
# Automatic 30-min refresh via the `pages-refresh` Docker service (reads the
# LIVE DB from the shared volume). Set these in .env:
#
# REQUIRED for the pages-refresh service — a GitHub token with write access to
# the Pages repo (fine-grained: Contents → Read/Write; or classic `repo`):
# GH_PAGES_TOKEN=github_pat_...
#
# Optional pages-refresh knobs (sensible defaults shown):
# PAGES_BASE_PATH=/market-brief      # URL sub-path; MUST equal the repo name
# PAGES_REPO=realzza/market-brief    # owner/name pushed to (gh-pages branch)
# REFRESH_INTERVAL=1800              # seconds between rebuilds
